The paper proposes a deep learning-based architecture for singular point detection in fingerprint images. This involves image processing and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves regression analysis, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of stacked hourglass networks, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) applications. Finally, the paper involves optimization techniques for improving the accuracy of the model, which falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
